Class Vector<RE extends IRingElement<RE>>

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.jlinalg.Vector<RE>
  • Type Parameters:
    RE - the type of the elements in the vector.
    All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable, java.lang.Comparable<Vector<RE>>

    public class Vector<RE extends IRingElement<RE>>
extends java.lang.Object
implements java.io.Serializable, java.lang.Comparable<Vector<RE>>
    This class represents a mathematical vector.
    Author:
    Andreas Keilhauer, Simon D. Levy, Georg Thimm

      • compareTo

        public int compareTo(Vector<RE> vector)
              throws InvalidOperationException
        Establish a lexicographical order between vectors. The order follows the following rules:
        • Comparison starts with the first vector element.
        • The first element that differs defines the order according to their numerical value.
        • if a null-value is found, the type of the fields is different, or the lengths of the vectors disagree, an exception is thrown
          Specified by:
          compareTo in interface java.lang.Comparable<Vector<RE extends IRingElement<RE>>>
          Parameters:
          vector -
          Returns:
          one of {<-1,0,>1} according to whether this vector is lexigrographically smaller, equal or bigger than the argument
          Throws:
          InvalidOperationException
